# Project Structure

This is a React + Vite + TypeScript portfolio app. Use the `@/` alias for
imports from `src` (e.g. `@/components/ui/Button`). Never use long relative
paths like `../../../`.

## Folders (`src/`)

- `components/` - shared, reusable components used across pages.
  - `components/layout/` - layout components (Header, Footer, Layout with
    `<Outlet />`). `usePageTracking()` lives here for automatic page views.
  - `components/ui/` - reusable UI primitives (Button, Card, Timeline, etc.).
  - `components/sketches/` - p5.js visual sketches for page backgrounds.
- `pages/` - page-level components mapped to routes (Home, About, Works,
  Blogs, BlogPost, Contact, Terms, Privacy, NotFound).
- `lib/` - cross-cutting utilities and third-party integration adapters
  (`analytics.ts`, `monitoring.ts`). Wrap external SDKs behind a thin
  interface here so call sites stay decoupled. Never import `@sentry/react`
  or call `window.gtag` outside of the adapters in `lib/`.
- `config/` - typed configuration. `env.ts` is the single source of truth for
  environment variables; do not read `import.meta.env` directly elsewhere.
- `hooks/` - shared hooks (useAnalytics, useMonitoring, usePageTracking,
  useTheme, useDirection, useNavbarToggle, etc.).
- `services/` - API clients (portfolio BFF API via TanStack Query + mappers).
- `constant/` - app constants and enums.
- `types/` - shared TypeScript types (analytics events, monitoring types,
  blog, menu, timeline).
- `utils/` - general utilities (i18n, dayjs, common helpers).
- `test/` - global Vitest setup and shared helpers.

## Conventions

- Component files use PascalCase matching the exported component name.
  Non-component files (configs, utilities, hooks) use camelCase.
- Tests live in a `__tests__/` folder at the same level as the code under test.
- New env vars: add to `src/config/env.ts`, `.env.example`, and
  `src/vite-env.d.ts`.
- User-facing strings go through i18n (`useTranslation`), never hardcoded.
